CH1

Then Sedrach lifted up his eyes to heaven and said with tears: “O Lord, why did You create man upon the earth? Why did You not command the earth to bring forth man as it brings forth beasts and cattle? It would have been better for man not to have been created than to live and sin and suffer eternal punishment. Why did You make man in Your image if You knew he would sin? Why did You breathe into him the breath of life knowing he would transgress Your commandments?”
The Lord said to Sedrach: “Sedrach, My beloved, I created man in My image and likeness so that he might inherit eternal life. But he transgressed My commandment and became subject to death. Yet I am merciful and do not desire the death of the sinner but that he should turn and live.”
Sedrach said: “Lord, have mercy on the sinners.”
Sedrach began to weep bitterly and said: “Woe is me, what have I done? O Lord God Almighty who made the heaven and the earth and all that is in them, why did You create man? Why did You make him upon the earth? Why did You not command the earth to bring forth man as it brings forth the other creatures? It would have been better if man had not been created than to live in this world and sin and suffer eternal torment.”

CH0 Introduction

Then the Lord placed Sedrach in Paradise and said to him: “Blessed are you Sedrach, for you have spoken with Me face to face. Go and tell the children of men to repent while there is still time, for My mercy is great but My judgment is also true.”
And Sedrach wept bitterly and said: “O Lord, have mercy upon the sinners, for the measure of Your compassion is greater than the sand of the sea and the stars of heaven.”
And the Lord answered Sedrach and revealed to him the measure of Paradise and the depths of His mercy, saying: “The soul of man is more precious to Me than all creation.”
Then Sedrach was taken up by an angel and brought before the throne of YHWH, where he pleaded for the salvation of sinners and questioned the severity of divine judgment.
In the days of the holy prophet Sedrach, while he prayed and fasted, the angel of the Lord appeared to him and carried him into the heavens to speak with the Most High.
